<item>
            <title>[LU-12695] A client panics if a request succeeded from Server but the following processing on the client failed.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12695</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A client panics if a request succeeded but the following processing failed.&lt;br/&gt;
The flow is below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
mdc_enqueue_base
 ldlm_cli_enqueue 
&#12288; ptlrpc_queue_wait      &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// succeeded, that is, req-&amp;gt;rq_transno != 0
&lt;/span&gt;  ldlm_cli_enqueue_fini  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// failed, that is, rc != 0
&lt;/span&gt;   ldlm_lock_change_resource &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// error ex. ENOMEM
&lt;/span&gt; mdc_clear_replay_flag
  LBUG &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &amp;lt;-&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are serveral ways that ldlm_cli_enqueue() may fail even if ldlm_cli_enqueue() succeeded. LBUG should be removed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
